-- Colombian Stock Movers: Almacenes Exito Drops; Grupo Sura Gains
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-20T21:37:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/colombian-stock-movers-almacenes-exito-drops-grupo-sura-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.2 percent to 13,499.58, while the
Colcap Index was little changed at 1,607.26.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  ,  Colombia ’s biggest publicly-
traded retailer, dropped 2 percent, the most in three months, to
24,960 pesos.  Colombia’s retail sales rose 1.3 percent in November from a
year earlier, the national statistics agency said yesterday
after the market closed. Economists had forecast a 5.9 percent
increase, according to the median estimate of 18 analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA  (GRUPOSUR CB), the
parent company of Colombia’s biggest bank, rose 1.5 percent to
31,360 pesos. The company said it will begin the regulatory
process to merge operations of its Colombian pension fund,
Proteccion SA, and ING Administradora de Pensiones y Cesantias
SA, according to a regulatory filing late yesterday.  The group, in the same filing, also denied reports that it
is planning to create a brokerage business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
